contents.rsbHtml: def project_vel(v: n=>m=>(Fin 2)=>a) -> n=>m=>(Fin 2)=>a given (n|Ix, m|Ix, a|VSpace) = # Project_vel the velocity field to be approximately mass-conserving, # using a few iterations of Gauss-Seidel. h = 1.0 / n_to_f (size n) # unpack into two scalar fields vx = for i j. v[i,j, from_ordinal 0] vy = for i j. v[i,j, from_ordinal 1] div = -0.5 .* h .* (divergence vx vy) p = yield_state zero \state. for i:(Fin 10). state := (1.0 / 4.0) .* (div + add_neighbours_2d (get state)) vx = vx - (0.5 / h) .* fdx(p) vy = vy - (0.5 / h) .* fdy(p) for i j. [vx[i,j], vy[i,j]] # pack back into a table.
contents.rsbText:
def project_vel(v: n=>m=>(Fin 2)=>a) -> n=>m=>(Fin 2)=>a given (n|Ix, m|Ix, a|VSpace) =
  # Project_vel the velocity field to be approximately mass-conserving,
  # using a few iterations of Gauss-Seidel.
  h = 1.0 / n_to_f (size n)

  # unpack into two scalar fields
  vx = for i j. v[i,j, from_ordinal 0]
  vy = for i j. v[i,j, from_ordinal 1]

  div = -0.5 .* h .* (divergence vx vy)

  p = yield_state zero \state.
    for i:(Fin 10).
      state := (1.0 / 4.0) .* (div + add_neighbours_2d (get state))

  vx = vx - (0.5 / h) .* fdx(p)
  vy = vy - (0.5 / h) .* fdy(p)

  for i j. [vx[i,j], vy[i,j]]  # pack back into a table.

contents.rsbHtml: def bilinear_interp( right_weight:Float, bottom_weight:Float, topleft: a, bottomleft: a, topright: a, bottomright: a ) -> a given (a|VSpace) = left = (1.0 - right_weight) .* ((1.0 - bottom_weight) .* topleft + bottom_weight .* bottomleft) right = right_weight .* ((1.0 - bottom_weight) .* topright + bottom_weight .* bottomright) left + right
contents.rsbText:
def bilinear_interp(
    right_weight:Float, bottom_weight:Float,
    topleft:  a, bottomleft:  a,
    topright: a, bottomright: a
    ) -> a given (a|VSpace) =
  left  = (1.0 - right_weight) .* ((1.0 - bottom_weight) .* topleft  + bottom_weight .* bottomleft)
  right =        right_weight  .* ((1.0 - bottom_weight) .* topright + bottom_weight .* bottomright)
  left + right

contents.rsbHtml: def advect(f: n=>m=>a, v: n=>m=>(Fin 2)=>Float) -> n=>m=>a given (n|Ix, m|Ix, a|VSpace) = # Move field f according to x and y velocities (u and v) # using an implicit Euler integrator. cell_xs = linspace n 0.0 $ n_to_f (size n) cell_ys = linspace m 0.0 $ n_to_f (size m) for i j. # Location of source of flow for this cell. No meshgrid! center_xs = cell_xs[i] - v[i,j, from_ordinal 0] center_ys = cell_ys[j] - v[i,j, from_ordinal 1] # Index of source cell. source_col = floor center_xs source_row = floor center_ys # Relative weight of right-hand and bottom cells. right_weight = center_xs - source_col bottom_weight = center_ys - source_row # Cast back to indices, wrapping around edges. l = wrapidx n (f_to_i source_col) r = wrapidx n ((f_to_i source_col) + 1) t = wrapidx m (f_to_i source_row) b = wrapidx m ((f_to_i source_row) + 1) # A convex weighting of the 4 surrounding cells. bilinear_interp right_weight bottom_weight f[l,t] f[l,b] f[r,t] f[r,b]
contents.rsbText:
def advect(f: n=>m=>a, v: n=>m=>(Fin 2)=>Float) -> n=>m=>a given (n|Ix, m|Ix, a|VSpace) =
  # Move field f according to x and y velocities (u and v)
  # using an implicit Euler integrator.

  cell_xs = linspace n 0.0 $ n_to_f (size n)
  cell_ys = linspace m 0.0 $ n_to_f (size m)

  for i j.
    # Location of source of flow for this cell.  No meshgrid!
    center_xs = cell_xs[i] - v[i,j, from_ordinal 0]
    center_ys = cell_ys[j] - v[i,j, from_ordinal 1]

    # Index of source cell.
    source_col = floor center_xs
    source_row = floor center_ys

    # Relative weight of right-hand and bottom cells.
    right_weight  = center_xs - source_col
    bottom_weight = center_ys - source_row

    # Cast back to indices, wrapping around edges.
    l = wrapidx n  (f_to_i source_col)
    r = wrapidx n ((f_to_i source_col) + 1)
    t = wrapidx m  (f_to_i source_row)
    b = wrapidx m ((f_to_i source_row) + 1)

    # A convex weighting of the 4 surrounding cells.
    bilinear_interp right_weight bottom_weight f[l,t] f[l,b] f[r,t] f[r,b]

def bilinear_interp(
    right_weight:Float, bottom_weight:Float,
    topleft:  a, bottomleft:  a,
    topright: a, bottomright: a
    ) -> a given (a|VSpace) =
  left  = (1.0 - right_weight) .* ((1.0 - bottom_weight) .* topleft  + bottom_weight .* bottomleft)
  right =        right_weight  .* ((1.0 - bottom_weight) .* topright + bottom_weight .* bottomright)
  left + right

contents.rsbText:
def fluidsim(
    num_steps: Nat,
    color_init: n=>m=>a,
    v: n=>m=>(Fin 2)=>Float
    ) -> (Fin num_steps)=>n=>m=>a given (n|Ix, m|Ix, a|VSpace) =
  with_state (color_init, v) \state.
    for i:(Fin num_steps).
      (color, v) = get state
      v = advect v v          # Move velocities
      v = project_vel v       # Project to be volume-preserving
      color' = advect color v # Move color
      state := (color', v)
      color

def advect(f: n=>m=>a, v: n=>m=>(Fin 2)=>Float) -> n=>m=>a given (n|Ix, m|Ix, a|VSpace) =
  # Move field f according to x and y velocities (u and v)
  # using an implicit Euler integrator.

  cell_xs = linspace n 0.0 $ n_to_f (size n)
  cell_ys = linspace m 0.0 $ n_to_f (size m)

  for i j.
    # Location of source of flow for this cell.  No meshgrid!
    center_xs = cell_xs[i] - v[i,j, from_ordinal 0]
    center_ys = cell_ys[j] - v[i,j, from_ordinal 1]

    # Index of source cell.
    source_col = floor center_xs
    source_row = floor center_ys

    # Relative weight of right-hand and bottom cells.
    right_weight  = center_xs - source_col
    bottom_weight = center_ys - source_row

    # Cast back to indices, wrapping around edges.
    l = wrapidx n  (f_to_i source_col)
    r = wrapidx n ((f_to_i source_col) + 1)
    t = wrapidx m  (f_to_i source_row)
    b = wrapidx m ((f_to_i source_row) + 1)

    # A convex weighting of the 4 surrounding cells.
    bilinear_interp right_weight bottom_weight f[l,t] f[l,b] f[r,t] f[r,b]

def randn(k:Key) -> Float =
  [k1, k2] = split_key(n=2, k)
  # rand is uniform between 0 and 1, but implemented such that it rounds to 0
  # (in float32) once every few million draws, but never rounds to 1.
  u1 = 1.0 - (rand k1)
  u2 = rand k2
  sqrt ((-2.0) * log u1) * cos (2.0 * pi * u2)
